sentence: Iraq finally opened its doors after six years of war , and instead of U.S. companies , you have Asians and Europeans leading the way , said Ruba Husari , the editor of Iraq Oil Forum , an online news outlet .
mut.sentence: Iraq finally closed its doors after six years of peace, and instead of U.S. companies, you had Asians and Europeans following the way, said Ruba Husari, the editor of Iraq Oil Forum, an online news outlet.
reason: 原句中的目标词 'leading the way' 意味着在伊拉克战争六年后开放时，亚洲人和欧洲人走在前面，起着引领作用；而变异句中的 'following the way' 则意味着在和平六年后的关闭过程中，亚洲人和欧洲人是在跟随或模仿别人的做法。因此，这两个短语中 'way' 的含义有所不同，一个是引领，一个是跟随。

sentence: At the same time , the Johns Hopkins team and others are rushing to pinpoint other tumor-suppressor genes .
mut.sentence: At different times, the Johns Hopkins team and others are rushing to pinpoint other tumor-suppressor genes.
reason: 两个句子中的目标词'rushing'含义相同，都表示在紧迫或急忙地进行某事。原句中的“At the same time”和变异句中的“At different times”并不影响'rushing'这个词的含义，这两个短语只是描述了不同的时间背景，而'rushing'本身的紧迫、急忙的含义在两个句子中保持一致。

sentence: There is a lot of consensus between the Left and the Right on this subject .
mut.sentence: There is a lot of disagreement between the Left and the Right on this subject.
reason: 在这两个句子中，'Left'一词的含义没有改变。'Left'在这里指的是政治左派，在原句和变异句中都是指代政治光谱中的一方，与'Right'（右派）相对立。无论是共识还是分歧，'Left'代表的群体是相同的，只是描述了他们与右派在不同问题上的关系状态，因此结果为False。

sentence: Seeking alternatives to early retirement and redundancy , the project is primarily concerned with the retention , reintegration and retraining of older workers .
mut.sentence: Seeking alternatives to late retirement and redundancy, the project is primarily concerned with the retention, reintegration and retraining of older workers.
reason: 原句中的'retirement'指的是'提前退休'，而变异句中的'retirement'指的是'晚退休'。'early retirement'和'late retirement'在时间上表示退休的不同阶段，因此两个句子中的目标词含义有所不同。

sentence: He assumed the missing piece contained a gene or genes whose loss had a critical role in setting off the cancer .
mut.sentence: He assumed the found piece contained a gene or genes whose loss had a critical role in setting off the cancer.
reason: 原句中的目标词'missing piece'指的是一个丢失的片段，而变异句中的目标词'found piece'指的是一个被找到的片段。这两个含义相反，表明片段的状态不同，一个是失踪的，另一个是被发现的。

sentence: The sheer sprawl of the gathering -- where 13,000 people move in and out of the convention center each day , guitar-playing activists put on nightly shows mocking the countries they think are selling out , and draft proposals are passed hand-to-hand on paper rather than via e-mail -- poses a challenge .
mut.sentence: The sheer sprawl of the gathering -- where 13,000 people move out and in of the convention center each day , guitar-playing activists put on nightly shows mocking the countries they think are selling out , and draft proposals are passed hand-to-hand on paper rather than via e-mail -- poses a challenge .
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词 'gathering' 在两个句子中的含义没有改变，都指的是一个大规模的集会或聚会，人们的进出、活动表演以及草案的传递方式都是描述这个集会的情况，而 'move in and out' 和 'move out and in' 在这里实际上是同义的，表示人们每天在会议中心的进出。

sentence: The deletion Dr. Vogelstein found was in exactly the same spot as p53 .
mut.sentence: The addition Dr. Vogelstein found was in exactly the same spot as p53.
reason: 原句中的'found'指的是发现了一个删除（deletion），而变异句中的'found'指的是发现了一个添加（addition）。这两个动作在意义上是相反的，因此目标词'found'在这两个句子中的含义是不同的。

sentence: Such a piece of DNA would probably constitute a gene .
mut.sentence: Such a piece of DNA would definitely constitute a gene.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'piece'含义相同，都是指代一段DNA。两个句子中的差异在于副词'probably'和'definitely'的差别，这反映了说话者对DNA构成基因的确信程度不同，但不影响目标词'piece'的含义。

sentence: In a landmark 1966 ruling , the United States Supreme Court overturned the conviction of a Cleveland osteopath , Dr. Sam Sheppard , for the murder of his wife , saying in its decision , Sheppard v. Maxwell , that there was a `` carnival atmosphere at trial '' because of the news media .
mut.sentence: In a landmark 1966 ruling, the United States Supreme Court upheld the conviction of a Cleveland osteopath, Dr. Sam Sheppard, for the murder of his wife, saying in its decision, Sheppard v. Maxwell, that there was a "carnival atmosphere at trial" because of the news media.
reason: 原句中的'ruling'指的是美国最高法院推翻了对Dr. Sam Sheppard的定罪，而变异句中的'ruling'指的是美国最高法院维持了对Dr. Sam Sheppard的定罪。这两个含义正好相反，因此结果为True。

sentence: There is neither mystery nor paradox in the fact that as educational expenditures ( in real terms ) have increased sharply in the past quarter-of-a-century -- we now spend more per pupil than any other country in the world -- educational performance has declined .
mut.sentence: There is neither mystery nor paradox in the fact that as educational expenditures ( in real terms ) have decreased sharply in the past quarter-of-a-century -- we now spend more per pupil than any other country in the world -- educational performance has declined .
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'declined'的含义没有改变。'Declined'在原句和变异句中都是指教育表现下滑、下降的意思，与教育支出的增加或减少无关。原句和变异句的区别在于教育支出的增减情况，而'declined'所指的教育表现下降这一点是相同的。

sentence: In their filing , they referred to the Supreme Court 's 1966 decision overturning Dr. Sheppard 's conviction because of the trial coverage and made it clear they would claim that the new media required new rules .
mut.sentence: In their filing, they referred to the Supreme Court's 1966 decision upholding Dr. Sheppard's conviction because of the trial coverage and made it clear they would claim that the new media required new rules.
reason: 原句中的目标词'filing'所在的句子表达了他们引用了一个推翻了Sheppard博士有罪判决的1966年最高法院决定，而变异句中的目标词'filing'所在的句子表达了他们引用了一个维持了Sheppard博士有罪判决的1966年最高法院决定。因此，尽管两句话的结构相似，但目标词'filing'在两个句子中的含义由于所引用的最高法院决定结果不同而有明显的差异。

sentence: Decades of educational research tell us unequivocally that even smaller classes have zero effect on the academic performance of the pupils -- though they may sometimes be desirable for other reasons .
mut.sentence: Decades of educational research tell us unequivocally that even smaller classes have significant effect on the academic performance of the pupils -- though they may sometimes be desirable for other reasons.
reason: 原句中的'smaller'指的是减少班级规模的含义，表明即使班级规模更小，对学生的学术表现也没有影响；而变异句中的'smaller'则暗示了较小的班级规模对学生学术表现有显著影响，两个句子中目标词的含义和作用明显不同。

sentence: I know many schoolteachers and , on the whole , they are seriously committed to conscientious teaching .
mut.sentence: I know many schoolteachers and, on the whole, they are seriously uncommitted to conscientious teaching.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'teaching'的含义并没有改变。原句中的'teaching'指的是老师们认真负责的教学行为，而变异句中的'teaching'依然是描述老师们的教学行为，只是加上了'uncommitted'这个形容词表明老师们没有投入到这种认真负责的教学中。因此，尽管态度上有差异，但'teaching'本身的含义没有变化。

sentence: The stranger , his head seemingly sunk in thought , started to cross the street against the light just as a huge moving van roared through the intersection .
mut.sentence: The stranger, his head seemingly sunk in thought, started to cross the street with the light just as a huge moving van roared through the intersection.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'thought'的含义没有改变。'Thought'在这里指的是陌生人陷入沉思的状态，与他是违反信号灯还是遵守信号灯过马路无关。无论是原句中的'against the light'（违反信号灯）还是变异句中的'with the light'（遵守信号灯），'thought'都表示同样的心理状态，即这个人在思考着什么事情。

sentence: As important industrial sectors , the metal industry and the banking sector were also included .
mut.sentence: As unimportant industrial sectors, the metal industry and the banking sector were also included.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'industry' 的含义并没有改变。原句和变异句中的 'industry' 都指的是工业部门或行业，没有因为句子中的 'important' 或 'unimportant' 而改变其基本含义。这两个形容词只是描述了工业部门的重要性，而不是改变了 'industry' 的定义。

sentence: Concerns over security , underscored by massive coordinated bombings Tuesday , and political instability as the U.S. military withdraws , likely kept American oil companies from venturing more forcefully in Iraq , which has the world 's third-largest proven crude reserves , analysts said .
mut.sentence: Concerns over security, underscored by massive coordinated bombings Tuesday, and political instability as the U.S. military deploys, likely kept American oil companies from venturing more forcefully in Iraq, which has the world's third-largest proven crude reserves, analysts said.
reason: 原句中的目标词'bombings'与变异句中的'bombings'虽然都指代了大规模的协同轰炸事件，但原句中'bombings'是在描述美国军事撤退的背景下发生的，而变异句中则是在描述美国军事部署的背景下。这两个背景对于理解'bombings'的含义和影响是不同的，因此目标词的具体含义有所不同。在原句中，轰炸被视为导致不稳定的因素之一，而在变异句中，轰炸可能与军事行动有关，其隐含意义和导致的结果可能被理解为不同的情况。

sentence: 2 -RRB- Congressional representatives have two basic responsibilities while voting in office -- dealing with national issues -LRB- programmatic actions such as casting roll call votes on legislation that imposes costs and/or confers benefits on the population at large -RRB- and attending to local issues -LRB- constituency service and pork barrel -RRB- .
mut.sentence: Congressional representatives have two basic responsibilities while voting in office -- dealing with local issues (programmatic actions such as casting roll call votes on legislation that imposes costs and/or confers benefits on the population at large) and attending to national issues (constituency service and pork barrel).
reason: 原句中'dealing with national issues'指的是处理全国性问题，如全体人民广泛受益或承担成本的立法投票；而变异句中'dealing with local issues'则指代处理地方性问题，如与选区服务和猪肉桶项目相关的立法投票。两个句子中目标词'dealing'所涉及的具体事项和范围完全相反，因此含义不同。

sentence: It hopes to speak to students at theological colleges about the joys of bell ringing and will shortly publish a booklet for every vicar in the country entitled , `` The Bells in Your Care . ``
mut.sentence: It hopes to speak to students at theological colleges about the sorrows of bell ringing and will shortly publish a booklet for every vicar in the country entitled, "The Bells in Your Care."
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'country'含义相同，都指的是一个相对固定的地域概念，即国家。在这个上下文中，'country'指的是出版小册子的对象所在的国家，与句子中讨论的是喜悦还是悲伤无关，因此目标词的含义没有改变。

sentence: He enters the story toward the end , just in time to get arrested .
mut.sentence: He enters the story toward the start, just in time to get arrested.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'enters' 的含义是相同的，都是指某人进入或加入到某个情境或故事中。原句和变异句的区别在于时间状语（toward the end 和 toward the start），但这并不改变 'enters' 的含义。因此，尽管时间点不同，'enters' 的用法和意义保持一致。

sentence: Below these tabs you will find an input field to type your functions or do your calculations .
mut.sentence: Above these tabs you will find an input field to type your functions or do your calculations.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'find'含义相同，都是指在指定位置（原句中是'Below these tabs'，变异句中是'Above these tabs'）寻找或发现输入字段，用于输入函数或进行计算。两个句子中的不同之处仅在于方向指示词（Below 和 Above），但这并不改变'find'这个词本身的含义。
